cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SE 

The paper focuses on the security aspect of the SCTP protocol and proposes new steganographic methods that can be applied to it. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of new SCTP features such as multi-homing and multi-streaming, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper may fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) as it discusses the hiding of information in a streaming protocol. Finally, the paper may also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it proposes new methods that can be used to hide information in an SCTP and discusses countermeasures to prevent such attacks.
